text: Qaem Shahr (; also known as Qā’em Shahr) is a city in Iran. It is the capital of Qaem Shahr County in the Mazandaran Province. The city had a population of 204,953 people in 2016. Before the Iranian revolution, the city was known as Shāhi (or Ŝâhi). == Notable people == * Mehrdad Oladi (1985 2016) - football player == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:Cities in Mazandaran Province
